cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a method for unsupervised feature learning, which falls under the category of machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for feature learning, which is a common technique in multimedia analysis. Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the issue of noisy clustering, which is a topic in cryptography and security. Hence, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
